                            td Fixed Assets
                            td Long-term assets such as printers.
                            td P&L is hit through depreciation, not full purchase cost at once.
                          tr
                            td 1590
                            td Accumulated Depreciation
                            td The total depreciation already charged against fixed assets.
                            td The depreciation expense line affects P&L.
              .col-lg-6
                .card.dark-surface.border-secondary.h-100
                  .card-body
                    h6.text-white Liabilities
                    p.text-muted-light.small Liabilities are amounts the business owes to suppliers, customers, or unpaid bills.
                    .table-responsive
                      table.table.table-sm.mb-0
                        thead
                          tr
                            th Code
                            th Account
                            th What It Means
                            th P&L Effect
                        tbody
                          tr
                            td 2000
                            td Supplier Payables
                            td Amount owed to suppliers, usually from credit purchases.
                            td No direct P&L effect; the related stock or expense creates the P&L effect.
                          tr
                            td 2100
                            td Accrued Payables
                            td Expenses recorded but not yet paid.
                            td P&L is hit when accrued; later payment only clears the liability.
                          tr
                            td 2200
                            td Customer Credits
                            td Money or credit balance the business owes to customers.
                            td No direct P&L effect when used; it clears receivables for orders.
              .col-lg-6
                .card.dark-surface.border-secondary.h-100
                  .card-body
                    h6.text-white Equity
                    p.text-muted-light.small Equity is the owner's/business value after liabilities are removed from assets. Profit increases it; drawings reduce it.
                    .table-responsive
                      table.table.table-sm.mb-0
                        thead
                          tr
                            th Code
                            th Account
                            th What It Means
                            th P&L Effect
                        tbody
                          tr
                            td 3000
                            td Owner Capital
                            td Money or assets invested into the business by the owner.
                            td No direct P&L effect; it increases business equity.
                          tr
                            td 3100
                            td Owner Drawings
                            td Money or assets taken out of the business by the owner.
                            td No direct P&L effect; it reduces business equity.
                          tr
                            td 3200
                            td Opening Balance Equity
                            td Net value from asset/liability balances that existed before the system started.
                            td No direct P&L effect; it helps the Balance Sheet show full business value.
              .col-lg-6
                .card.dark-surface.border-secondary.h-100
                  .card-body
                    h6.text-white Revenue
                    p.text-muted-light.small Revenue is income earned from jobs/orders. Revenue increases profit.
                    .table-responsive
                      table.table.table-sm.mb-0
                        thead
                          tr
                            th Code
                            th Account
                            th What It Means
                            th P&L Effect
                        tbody
                          tr
                            td 4000
                            td Sales Revenue
                            td Income earned when orders/jobs are created.
                            td Increases P&L revenue and profit.
                          tr
                            td 4050
                            td Supplier Debit Adjustments
                            td Other income from supplier account debit adjustments.
                            td Increases P&L revenue/other income.
              .col-lg-6
                .card.dark-surface.border-secondary.h-100
                  .card-body
                    h6.text-white Cost & Expenses
                    p.text-muted-light.small Costs and expenses reduce profit. Cost of sales relates directly to jobs; operating expenses support the business.
                    .table-responsive
                      table.table.table-sm.mb-0
                        thead
                          tr
                            th Code
                            th Account
                            th What It Means
                            th P&L Effect
                        tbody
                          tr
                            td 5000
                            td Material Cost of Sales
                            td Cost of stock/materials consumed by jobs.
                            td Reduces gross profit.
                          tr
                            td 5100
                            td Out-sourced Cost of Sales
                            td Cost payable to artists/partners handling outsourced jobs.
                            td Reduces gross profit.
                          tr
                            td 5200
                            td Printer Depreciation
                            td Usage or monthly depreciation charged for production printers.
                            td Reduces gross profit when tied to production.
                          tr
                            td 6000
                            td Rent Expense
                            td Rent cost released or recorded for the period.
                            td Reduces net profit.
                          tr
                            td 6100
                            td Staff Expense
                            td Salary or staff-related cost.
                            td Reduces net profit.
                          tr
                            td 6200
                            td Utilities / Electricity Expense
                            td Electricity, water, and related utility costs.
                            td Reduces net profit.
                          tr
                            td 6300
                            td Internet / Data Expense
                            td Internet and data cost.
                            td Reduces net profit.
                          tr
                            td 6400
                            td Fixed Asset Depreciation
                            td Straight-line depreciation for non-printer assets such as tables, chairs, computers, or fixtures.
                            td Reduces net profit as an operating expense.
                          tr
                            td 6900
                            td General Expense
                            td Other business expenses.
                            td Reduces net profit.
            .mt-3
              h6.text-white Common Journal Examples
              .table-responsive
                table.table.table-sm.table-hover.mb-0
                  thead
                    tr
                      th Event
                      th Debit
                      th Credit
                      th Meaning
                  tbody
                    tr
                      td Order created
                      td Accounts Receivable
                      td Sales Revenue
                      td Customer owes the business and revenue is earned.
                    tr
                      td Customer pays cash/bank/MoMo
                      td Cash and Bank Books
                      td Accounts Receivable
                      td Cash increases and customer debt reduces.
                    tr
                      td Order paid from account credit
                      td Customer Credits
                      td Accounts Receivable
                      td Customer credit reduces and order debt clears.
                    tr
                      td Stock purchased
                      td Inventory / Stock
                      td Cash or Supplier Payables
                      td Stock asset increases; cash reduces or supplier debt increases.
                    tr
                      td Stock used for jobs
                      td Material Cost of Sales
                      td Inventory / Stock
                      td Inventory reduces and job cost appears in P&L.
                    tr
                      td Accrued expense recorded
                      td Expense account
                      td Accrued Payables
                      td P&L is hit now, payment happens later.
                    tr
                      td Accrued expense paid
                      td Accrued Payables
                      td Cash and Bank Books
                      td Liability clears and cash reduces; P&L is not hit again.
                    tr
                      td Prepaid expense released
                      td Expense account
                      td Prepaid Expenses
                      td Future-paid cost is moved into current P&L.
                    tr
                      td Owner invests cash
                      td Cash and Bank Books
                      td Owner Capital
                      td Cash and business equity increase; no P&L effect.
                    tr
                      td Owner withdraws cash
                      td Owner Drawings
                      td Cash and Bank Books
                      td Cash and business equity reduce; no P&L effect.
                    tr
                      td Opening asset recorded
                      td Asset account
                      td Opening Balance Equity
                      td Existing business value is added without affecting P&L.
